Data Analyst

Remote Working

We are looking for an enthusiastic and driven Data Analyst. The successful candidate will drive business improvements through use of data to provide key insights which inform business decisions.

Working with the team, the post-holder will assist in the development of systems to provide effective data capture and analysis against existing datasets.

The post holder will be comfortable working with large amounts of data toorganise, categorise and classify it to make it more effective and usable.

The role will consist of:
• Developing and implementing databases, data collection systems, data analytics and other strategies that optimise statistical efficiency and quality;
• Using data and analysing results using statistical techniques and providing ongoing reports;
• Interpreting trends in complex data sets to identify and assess key risks for our lifecycle fund;
• Filtering and "cleaning" data in order to align datasets and provide meaningful... comparators;
• Working with the team to prioritise information needs and present salient trend analysis that assists business decisions;
• Identifying and defining new process improvement opportunities.

Qualifications or Required Experience:
• Proven working experience as a Data Analyst or Business Data Analyst
• Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques;
• Strong knowledge of and experience with reporting packages (Business Objects, Operational Decision Manager, Power BI etc), databases (SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks would be desirable but not essential);
• Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analysing datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc);
• Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organise, analyse, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy;
• Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings;
• BS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics desireable

Salary and Benefits:

You will be working for a modern, forward-thinking business; that believes the strengths, skills and personalities of their people are the key to the groups success. This is a full time, permanent role for which you will receive a competitive salary and bonus scheme as well as role dependant additional benefits.

To be considered for this Data Analyst role, please apply and we will contact you as soon as possible.

